<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06235167 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06235167 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; FOOTBALL; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Ray Handley, the mathematics whiz from Stanford who coaches the New YorkGiants, went against conventional thinking and tradition Wednesday, namingJeff Hostetler as his quarterback over Phil Simms.;   After considering allthe X's and O's and statistics, ending months of speculation, Handley citedthis non-scientific reason:  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  HANDLEY SELECTS HOSTETLER OVER SIMMS AS GIANTS' QB  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  NFL Notebook  </MEMO><TEXT>     &quot;It's a gut reaction on my part as much as anything else.&quot;;   Simms, 35,figured to have the edge because of his experience, and, traditionally, astarter isn't unseated by the man who replaced him only because of an injury.;  Hostetler, 30, took over for the injured Simms last season and helped theGiants to a Super Bowl victory. Along the way, the Giants beat the 49ers andChicago Bears, which also figured into Handley's equation.;   &quot;Jeff gives usan excellent opportunity in two of the first three games,&quot; Handley said.;  The Giants open their season against the 49ers on Sept. 2. Two weeks later,they face the Bears.;   The Giants are 2-9 in games Simms has started againstthe 49ers and Bears.; ETC.: Los Angeles Raiders defensive end Scott Davissigned a three-year contract that averages $700,000 per season. . . . The NFLapproved a plan that establishes practice squads of three to five players foreach team during the 1991 season. . . . The Detroit Lions acquired widereceiver Brett Perriman from the New Orleans Saints for a 1992 draft pick.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910822  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  12G  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  